Concepts of personnel management and talent management; areas of personnel management and its relations to internal and external environments of an organisation; planning of human resources, hiring and choosing of employees; motivating and remunerating; staff development and career management; trends in personnel management.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To develop knowledge and an understanding of the principles of personnel management, and skills to apply them.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has completed the course: - knows the nature of personnel management, talent management and career management and understands the importance of these in an organisation;  - knows the principles of personnel planning, hiring of employees, evaluation, development and motivation, and is able to apply them;  - is able to analyse and ethically resolve cases related to personnel management, and use relevant sources of information; - is able to present his/her opinion in a reasoned manner, including in a digital environment.
